data.name: Crystal Orchestra by Goldweard x Logan Nelson
data.description:
Goldweard and Logan Nelson have teamed up for their first collaboration of The Crystal Orchestra. Envisioned as the first major 'classical' music NFT, The Crystal Orchestra bridges together the performances of 15 live musicians together in the form of crystal instruments. These instruments, when layered with the rest of their section, form live ensembles with a conductor. And to show our support for the community of collectors behind our work, we’ve set royalties at 0% for life. Try and collect your favorite orchestra section!

Logan Nelson scores compositions that evoke thrilling textures unique to each project. This collaboration with Goldweard emphasizes his style of incorporating live, virtuosic musicians in his music. His original scores can be heard on film and television projects like Apple TV’s The Morning Show, Netflix’s Dear White People, and projects for National Geographic, Sony, and Showtime.

data.name: Cunning Wolf Society CWS
data.description: The Society is home to 5009 NFT ERC-721 Wolf identities living in the Metaverse, their consciousness hosted on the Ethereum blockchain. Each identity is unique and algorithmically generated from over 130 possible traits. Some Wolves are more rare, but all are uniquely dope. Wolves are beings with a purpose, hungry for learning and with a burning desire for conquering the status quo. One of their main qualities is the willingness to withstand the foolish optimism that permeates the NFT realm and embrace rational optimism; that is, we’re not all going to make it, only those who choose the noble path of unplugging from the hive-mind. Wolves are descendants of Geri and Freki; willing to sacrifice anything in pursuit of the upmost admirable purpose - knowledge - nothing can stand in their path. We are the Cunning Wolves.

Curious Cabins is a 1/1 collection of isometric houses, hand drawn by Stefan Große Halbuer. The Cabins artworks base on a fascination for whimsical architecture as well as isometric illustration. data.name: Curse NFT
data.description:
Accursed Share’s genesis piece, the 1/1 Curse NFT, is a 4K 3D-image of Krystall Schott produced by PROTAGON, the visual effects wizards for Marvel. It is the first NFT to integrate Chainlink’s revolutionary Keeper technology to create the first dynamic NFT to evolve in response to the changing price of Ethereum.

Curse NFT will have five different presentations. When the price of ETH goes up for 1 and 2 days in a row, the NFT will display positive 3D renderings. When the price of ETH decreases for 1 and 2 days in a row, the displays will be negative. Finally, when the price of ETH hits 20K, Krystall’s face will be displayed in its full blessed form.

Rarity & Price 
Melchior - 0.025
Bronze - 0.05 
Silver - 0.1

💛 An intergalactic hug for everyone.

Inspired by Paul.

Melchior - 0.025
Bronze - 0.05 
Silver - 0.1 
Gold - 0.15 
Special - *

You will get a vector image with the purchase, which will allow you to transfer the alien to the real world without losing quality (you can print it on a mug or T-shirt, etc.). When you collect 10 aliens, you can apply to get one for free. The free alien will be selected randomly and it will be sent to your collection.

*Collaborations will not have a vector file as they will be executed in raster graphics or other format.

💛 An intergalactic hug for everyone.

Inspired by Paul.

data.name: Cyber Rexes
data.description:
Alternative reality where dinosaurs didn't go extinct and now roam the earth freely. Earth is now ruled by the T-Rex elite called "Cyber Rexes".

Cyber Rexes are a set of 5.000 unique collectibles living on Ethereum blockchain ( or Cyber Earth if you will ). Almost all of 5.000 Rexes have been generated by our algorithm, but some have been made completely by hand and have a set of traits like no other Rexes ( also we have included some pretty sick gifs ). Since blockchain is immutable there is absolutely no way to create more Cyber Rexes ever again. Each NFT can be assigned a unique name, this means that only one Cyber Rex can have a name for example "Tyrannosaurus". This provides another level of scarcity for fearsome Rexes.

data.name: CyberTime2188
data.description:
We are developing the ecosystem CyberTime2188 where art and DeFi technologies are intertwined. The ecosystem consists of 3 main products:

1. CyberTime NFT Store. 
With this product, we have decided to digitalize the time. We have broken down 24 hours into 86400 seconds and transformed them into the NFT assets. 

2. NFT Staking Generator & Governance Token CTmS
Holders can stake it and get the opportunity to receive governance token CTmS. 
CTmS (CyberTime MilliSeconds) is the governance token at this platform with voting rights on decisions that influence the platform development. 

3. NFT Lending Marketplace. 
The marketplace allows digital token holders to get access to liquidity without losing their NFT assets, and it allows lenders to get profits with a secured provision in the form of liquid NFT assets.

data.name: Cyclical Project
data.description:
Animated art, generated entirely with p5.js code that is backed up and stored on chain.

The 2nd EVER user-created project on Sunflower Industries.

Abstract, animated, generative art that meditates upon the cyclical nature of reality.

From every breath we take to the spinning of the planets, the repetition of cycles binds time and the universe together.

Mirroring this, a loop of code creates these rotating pieces by printing circles in repeated, rotational symmetry.

data.name: CycloTurtles | NE
data.description:
Welcome to The CycloVerse

The worlds before man hosted an array of fantastical creatures beyond our comprehension. Planet earth was the link between these CycloWorlds where all creatures lived in harmony.

The 4 masters of the CycloVerse closed all portals to protect their own kind as the worlds plunged into chaos and planet earth was thrown into disarray.

YOU, an adventurer made it your life’s purpose to re-connect these CycloWorlds. When all hope was lost you uncovered the emergence of one of these portals. How was it re-opened? What’s on the other side? 

As you step into the portal You gain access to the CycloTurtle Tribe stored as ERC-721 tokens on the Ethereum blockchain. This collection of 7777 CycloTurtles, all equipped with unique attributes grants you the ability to obtain the knowledge and powers of the Cyclo-Turtles. Find your way into each CycloTurtle island by harnessing the power of your  unique personal collection of CycloTurtles.

data.name: Damien Hirst - Great Expectations
data.description:
HENI is delighted to present The Great Expectations NFT collection which contains 10,000 unique artworks made by Damien Hirst. Following on from the artwork that he created for Drake's album cover, the NFTs show grids of emoji-like pregnant women whose forms have been constructed from spots of various shapes, sizes and colors taken directly from The Currency artworks themselves. The NFTs were airdropped to holders of The Currency, Damien Hirst's first NFT collection.

The collection is on the Palm blockchain, which is a new token-powered ecosystem for NFTs connected to Ethereum. It is 99% more energy efficient than proof of work systems such as Ethereum or Bitcoin. The Great Expectations NFTs can be moved to Ethereum.

Reimagining the way NFTs are used, The Currency is a collection of 10,000 NFTs which correspond to 10,000 unique physical artworks which are stored in a secure vault in the UK. The works are now brought to life through their launch on the blockchain.

Starting with the creation of the physical artworks in 2016, The Currency explores the boundaries of art and currency—when art changes and becomes a currency, and when currency becomes art. Successful applicants will all initially receive NFTs. Ultimately, you have to decide between the digital NFT or the physical artwork, both of which are artworks in their own right. Whichever you pick, the other gets burned.

The collection is on the Palm blockchain, which is a new token-powered ecosystem for NFTs connected to Ethereum. It is 99% more energy efficient than proof of work systems such as Ethereum or Bitcoin. The Currency NFTs can be moved to Ethereum.

data.name: Daniel Arsham
data.description:
Daniel Arsham is a contemporary American visual artist who works across art, architecture, and performance. His work has been shown in museums and institutions worldwide, including MoMA PS1 and the New Museum, New York among others. He is the subject of a solo exhibition at Musée Guimet in Paris, and a forthcoming solo show at UCCA Dune in July 2021. Arsham’s work was also recently included in The National Gallery of Victoria’s NGV Triennial 2020.

Since 2013, Daniel has developed a highly successful edition practice with global reach, becoming one of the key leaders in this space. His releases often sell out immediately, resulting in exponential secondary market results on StockX and at auction houses such as Sotheby's. Arsham has also collaborated with the likes of Adidas, Dior, Pharrell Williams, and Pokémon.

data.description: i am a traveling salesman for my family business. located in the northeast of north america. i constantly find myself in awe of the beauty around me while i'm on the road but with no time to stop. a big part of my life is inspired from behind the dashboard. so i began to create while traveling from the drivers seat. this collection of images depicts the behind the scenes of both my work and running the space "gm we love the photographers" M-F 8:30-11 a.m. est. || this is a growing collection over the course of the year. there will be 13 images per season (winter,spring,summer,fall) 1 rare image per season (you'll have to figure out which one it is). each image will depict 1 week of the year. each image has been paired with a song to further that function of the mood and depict my personal emotion. all will be minted on my own smart contract! after purchase you will receive 1. a link to the song paired to the image. 2. digital download of the image. 3. my gratitude from me and my family

data.name: Dave Pollot
data.description: Dave Pollot is NY based artist and former software engineer known for his seamless addition of contemporary life/pop culture icons into traditional backgrounds (most often using oil paints and found/thrifted paintings). What initially began as a joke between him and his wife in 2012 quickly became a desire to answer a question: Could he change the meaning of an unwanted piece of artwork without drastically altering its aesthetic and make it wanted again? Since that time he’s completed hundreds of paintings and his work has been displayed and found in homes, galleries, businesses, and private collections in all 50 states and in over 40 countries around the world. His work has attracted attention from the media both in the U.S. and abroad, including Business Insider, Instagram, Hypebeast, HiFructose, the SyFy Channel, and more. His corporate clients include SONY, Instagram, McDonalds, New Balance, and others.

data.name: David Ariew X Tatler China
data.description:
In partnership with *Tatler China* and the artist [David Ariew](https://twitter.com/DavidAriew), TR Lab is pleased to announce the online sale of David's NFT artwork, *Fractal Monarch*. This collaboration marks a milestone: when a still image from David Ariew's digital artwork *Fractal Monarch* appears on the cover of *Tatler China*, it marks the first NFT to do so on a Chinese magazine. TR Lab is honored to facilitate the sale of the artwork, and half of the sale proceeds will be donated to global nonprofit organization Save The Children Hong Kong.

David Ariew's *Fractal Monarch* depicts a futuristic digital insect rendered in black and gold to correspond with Tatler's theme colors. The work was inspired by the phenomenon of the butterfly effect, and symbolizes how a small contribution can make a large impact on a child's future.

data.name: David OReilly x Flying Lotus
data.description:
Flying Lotus' name is synonymous with creative innovation, having released six seminal studio albums, a slew of audio-visual marvels and, in the process, gaining a Grammy for his work on Thundercat's 'It Is What It Is'. The multi-disciplinary Los Angeles artist has remained in constant orbit, collaborating with Kendrick Lamar on the classic To Pimp a Butterfly, directing and writing the Sundance-premiered comic horror hallucination Kuso, and producing much of Thundercat’s Drunk.

David OReilly is an Irish artist based in Los Angeles. A computer graphics pioneer, his animated works influenced a generation of 3d art, winning awards at Berlin, Venice, Sundance, Clermont Ferrand and many others. David created the futuristic games in Spike Jonze’s Academy Award winning film Her, and went on to develop the iconic game Mountain and universe simulation Everything - the first realtime project to qualify for an Oscar.

data.name: Dawn Key
data.description:
The Dawn Key gives access to Spectra.art's highest tier of utility.

# How to Activate

Collectors of the Dawn Key must hold the following 6 Dawn Trilogy pieces for the key to be active:

3 x [Eternal Fragments](https://opensea.io/collection/eternal-fragments)
2 x [Vortex](https://opensea.io/collection/vortex-spectra-art)
1 x [Chromospheres](https://opensea.io/collection/chromospheres)

# Benefits and Utility

1. Guaranteed presale mint and a 50% discount to Shackled, the FIRST ever fully on-chain 3D rendering engine.

2. Priority access to our collaboration with Eponym by ART AI

3. Priority access and discounts on future projects. Details on these are yet to be publicly announced, but in line with the Spectra ethos, rest assured we'll be looking to continue pushing the frontier of technological innovation in the space.

# About the Art

The Dawn Key is a hand-made 1/1 piece by Ike, incorporating 3D visual assets from each Dawn Trilogy collection.
